      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR BRAVE LINI (7) stepped up to 2150m for the first time last start and did a good job to finish third after giving away a big start on the corner at this track. Like the eight-day back-up and the blinkers coming off. Likely to improve off that last run which should be good enough to take this out. BENZINO (1) had been racing well without winning but broke through last time with a massive 6.2-length win over 2070m in a maiden at Doomben, leading throughout. More depth to this but the manner of that victory is hard to ignore. FIRM AGREEMENT (2) has raced twice this prep and been beaten a long way on each occasion in Sydney. Placed two from three third-up and this is a huge class drop. Definite contender. MONTEVECCHIO (4) appreciated the step up to 2450m at Beaudesert last start where he worked home well to grab second. Just one win in 34 is alarming. Exotics only. CLASSIC SHIRAZ (6) just missed at Casino last time and this longer journey will suit.",
